Author and food personality dies at age 67. Twitter/@dorahlydia JOHANNESBURG - Chef, and former True Love editor, Dorah Sitole had died. The 67-year-old passed away on Monday Morning. She is the award winning author of two books, 'Cooking from Cape to Cairo', and, '40 years of iconic food'. READ: Lesego Semenya releases new cookbook It is still unclear what caused Sitole's death. Her publishers say they will be releasing a statement shortly.